              <DefinitionShort>a period of seven days</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>week</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In some languages it may be better to render {S:04201801200008} as simply ‘for every seven days, I fast two days.’ For the expression ‘the first day of the week,’ there may be a number of complications, especially since in present-day usage Monday is often regarded as ‘the first day of the week.’ For the NT, of course, the Sabbath Day, or ‘Saturday,’ marked the seventh day of the week and the next day would be regarded as ‘the first day of the week,’ namely, Sunday.</Comments>
